<Lecture>
    <Description>
        We can also use keyword synchronized in the method name as below: So two are same:
    </Description><CodeSnipped>
    private void incrementAndReport() {
        synchronized(this) {
            System.out.print((++sheepCount)+" ");
        }
    }

</CodeSnipped><CodeSnipped>
    private synchronized void incrementAndReport() {
        System.out.print((++sheepCount)+" ");
    }
</CodeSnipped>
    <Description>
        It can also be used for static methods.
    </Description>
</Lecture>

